ategist at National Securities Corp.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Commit=
tee members have a few rules they follow when deciding to make changes in t=
he S&amp;P 500. Companies being added to the index must be highly liquid U.=
S. firms with a market capitalization of at least $13.1 billion, for instan=
ce. Moreover, the committee has leeway in deciding on changes.</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They also have to meet profitability requi=
