 markets and for just, like, stocks go up 1,000% in a week and nobody can e=
xplain why and the whole thing looks sort of dumb and Congress asks the SEC=
 about it and the SEC has no satisfying explanation. But the SEC can=E2=80=
=99t just say =E2=80=9Call this retail trading is dumb, stop it.=E2=80=9D I=
t can=E2=80=99t say that because that is sort of impolitic and un-American;=
 if American freedom means anything, it means the unfettered right to day-t=
rade stocks on your phone for free. It also can=E2=80=99t say that because =
it doesn=E2=80=99t really have the regulatory apparatus to do it. You can=
=E2=80=99t, like, ban retail trading.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And s=
o the SEC does things like <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
